name: Equatable
desc: A type that can be compared for value equality.

items.name: static func == (Self, Self) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are equal.

items.name: static func != (Self, Self) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are not equal.

items.name: func == ((), ()) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the corresponding components of two tuples are equal.

items.name: func == <A, B>((A, B), (A, B)) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the corresponding components of two tuples are equal.

items.name: func == <A, B, C>((A, B, C), (A, B, C)) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the corresponding components of two tuples are equal.

items.name: func == <A, B, C, D>((A, B, C, D), (A, B, C, D)) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the corresponding components of two tuples are equal.

items.name: func == <A, B, C, D, E>((A, B, C, D, E), (A, B, C, D, E)) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the corresponding components of two tuples are equal.

items.name: func == <A, B, C, D, E, F>((A, B, C, D, E, F), (A, B, C, D, E, F)) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the corresponding components of two tuples are equal.

items.name: func != ((), ()) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether any corresponding components of the two tuples are not equal.

items.name: func != <A, B>((A, B), (A, B)) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether any corresponding components of the two tuples are not equal.

items.name: func != <A, B, C>((A, B, C), (A, B, C)) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether any corresponding components of the two tuples are not equal.

items.name: func != <A, B, C, D>((A, B, C, D), (A, B, C, D)) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether any corresponding components of the two tuples are not equal.

items.name: func != <A, B, C, D, E>((A, B, C, D, E), (A, B, C, D, E)) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether any corresponding components of the two tuples are not equal.

items.name: func != <A, B, C, D, E, F>((A, B, C, D, E, F), (A, B, C, D, E, F)) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether any corresponding components of the two tuples are not equal.

items.name: func ~= <T>(T, T) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two arguments match by value equality.
